  "text": "Using (4) and (5) with all the characters in the CASIA-OLHWDB1.0 dataset [CITATION_1] , Fig. 3 illustrates the effect on the distribution of strokes. With DropStroke, the number of generated characters increases more than 5,000-fold, from 1.6×10 6 to 8.5×10 [CITATION_2] , demonstrating considerable augmentation. In addition, the DropStroke method breaks the original stroke structure and prevents structural information from being considered; these personal stroke structures may to some extent lead to better identification, but they limit the generalization",
